	<refsect1>
		<title>Introduction</title>
		<para>
			Anansi is a web crawler which is designed to operate in clusters of
			parallel processing nodes. Originally developed as a generic web
			crawling framework, it is bundled with modules to support its
			specific use as part of the <link xlink:href="https://bbcarchdev.github.io/res/">Research &amp; Education Space</link>.
		</para>
		<para>
			Anansi is open source software, released under the terms of the
			<cite><citetitle><link xlink:href="http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0">Apache License, 2.0</link></citetitle></cite>.
			The public Git repository for Anansi is hosted at <link xlink:href="https://github.com/bbcarchdev/anansi">Github</link>.
		</para>
	</refsect1>
